> Unlike common object-oriented GUI frameworks, Ribir widgets do not need to inherit a base class or hold a base object. It is a pure composition modelI'm really not sure how this "composition" is any different to the usual inheritance you see in frameworks like QML *in practice*.This in Ribir:```Column {        align_items: Align::Center,

        item_gap: 12.,

        @H1 { text: "Todo" }
}```Would be this in QML:```ColumnLayout {        spacing: 12

        Text {
                Layout.alignment: Qt.AlignHCenter

                text: "Todo"

                font.pointSize: 17
        }

}```
